name: Darkness
description:
I caught the darkness
It was drinking from your cup
I caught the darkness
Drinking from your cup
I said, "Is this contagious?"
You said, "Just drink it up."

( L.Cohen )

Ireland again.
I love that hour of the night, when most people leave their masks and the costume of the character they are used to playing during the day. It is a good hour to begin to exist.
And Dublin is a city where 1 a.m. tastes even more special. Stout, whisky, cigarettes and musicians. Here, we know that joy and melancholy are two sisters that must be embraced in turn.
I like to take obscure photos of these atmospheres, the sharpness and the technique are brakes to the deployment of the memory of this gaze. Failed, imperfect, marked with regret for a perfection dreamed of, fantasized. These are the photos that I like.
